1.  change app name to app.py
2.  go to Heroku CLI
3.  download Heroku CLI
4.  exit window shell & restart 
5.  set environment back on
6.  check version:  heroku -v
7.  (we need to reset development environment) by typing:
8.  pip install gunicorn
9.  pip install psycopg2
10.	pip freeze
11. pip freeze > requirements.txt
12. echo web: gunicorn app:app > Procfile
13. Log In to Heroku:  heroku login
	(to check addon plans: heroku addons:plans heroku-postgresql)

14. Create a heroku app:   heroku create flaskintro2
15. copy/paste url to web browser: https://flaskintro2-f3d9f3959b90.herokuapp.com/

16. push our app and database:
heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:essential-0 --app flaskintro2

